See the end for copying conditions.

The contributors that suggested a given feature is shown in [].
	
This uses outline mode in Emacs.  See C-h m [M-x describe-mode].

* Changes in Unix::Processors 2.022 09/13/2004

****	Documentation updates.

* Changes in Unix::Processors 2.021 04/05/2004

***	Hyperthreading detection added for FreeBSD [by Daniel Gustafson]

* Changes in Unix::Processors 2.020 03/04/2004

**	Added max_physical for detecting number of CPUs ignoring
	hyperthreading.

* Changes in Unix::Processors 2.015 01/27/2004

****	Documentation fixes.

* Changes in Unix::Processors 2.014 05/12/2003

***	Irix/FreeBSD port fixes. [by Daniel Gustafson]

* Changes in Unix::Processors 2.013 05/05/2003

***	Add support for SGI Irix and some FreeBSD. [by Daniel Gustafson]

* Changes in Unix::Processors 2.011 01/02/2003

***	Fix type and frequency for AIX and HPUX. [by Reid Madsen]

* Changes in Unix::Processors 2.010 12/30/2002

**	Added support for AIX, HPUX, MIPS, Alpha. [by Reid Madsen]

****	Major version bump only because '1.10' < '1.9'

* Changes in Unix::Processors 1.9 8/30/2002

****	README updates

* Changes in Unix::Processors 1.8 2/13/2001

****	Makefile.PL updates for testing

* Changes in Unix::Processors 1.7 1/21/2000

****	VERSION into Processors.pm, AUTHOR into Makefile.PL

* Changes in Unix::Processors 1.6 1/17/2000

**	First CPAN Release

